      "authorityKey": "cdfw",
      "retrievedDate": "2026-07-01",
      "quotedText": "(154) Truckee River (Nevada, Placer, and Sierra cos.). (A) Truckee River for 1,000 feet below the Lake Tahoe outlet dam. Closed to all fishing all year. (B) Truckee River from the confluence of Trout Creek downstream to the mouth of Prosser Creek. All year. Only artificial flies with barbless hooks may be used. 0 trout. (C) Truckee River from the mouth of Prosser Creek downstream to the Nevada State Line. Last Saturday in Apr. through Nov. 15. Only artificial lures may be used. 2 trout. Nov. 16 through the Friday preceding the last Saturday in Apr. Only artificial lures with barbless hooks may be used. 0 trout."
    },
